parameters.name: event.metaEvent.entry
parameters.description: entry, for example: `"Starting Skaffold: {Version:v0.39.0-16-g5bb7c9e0 ConfigVersion:skaffold/v1 GitVersion: GitCommit:5bb7c9e078e4d522a5ffc42a2f1274fd17d75902 GitTreeState:dirty BuildDate01:29Z GoVersion:go1.13rc1 Compiler:gc Platform:linux/amd64}"`.

parameters.name: event.metaEvent.metadata.build.type
parameters.description:
- UNKNOWN_BUILD_TYPE: Could not determine Build Type
 - CLUSTER: Cluster Build
 - GCB: GCB Build
 - LOCAL: Local Build

parameters.name: event.metaEvent.metadata.deploy.cluster
parameters.description:
- UNKNOWN_CLUSTER_TYPE: Could not determine Cluster Type
 - MINIKUBE: Minikube Cluster
 - GKE: GKE cluster
 - OTHER: All Cluster except Minikube and GKE

parameters.name: event.buildEvent.errCode
parameters.description:
- OK: A default status code for events that do not have an associated phase.
Typically seen with the DevEndEvent event on success.
 - STATUSCHECK_SUCCESS: Status Check Success
 - BUILD_SUCCESS: Build Success
 - DEPLOY_SUCCESS: Deploy Success
 - BUILD_PUSH_ACCESS_DENIED: Build error due to push access denied
 - BUILD_PROJECT_NOT_FOUND: Build error due to GCP project not found.
 - STATUSCHECK_IMAGE_PULL_ERR: Container image pull error
 - STATUSCHECK_CONTAINER_CREATING: Container creating error
 - STATUSCHECK_RUN_CONTAINER_ERR: Container run error
 - STATUSCHECK_CONTAINER_TERMINATED: Container is already terminated
 - STATUSCHECK_DEPLOYMENT_ROLLOUT_PENDING: Deployment waiting for rollout
 - STATUSCHECK_CONTAINER_RESTARTING: Container restarting error
 - STATUSCHECK_UNHEALTHY: Readiness probe failed
 - STATUSCHECK_NODE_MEMORY_PRESSURE: Node memory pressure error
 - STATUSCHECK_NODE_DISK_PRESSURE: Node disk pressure error
 - STATUSCHECK_NODE_NETWORK_UNAVAILABLE: Node network unavailable error
 - STATUSCHECK_NODE_PID_PRESSURE: Node PID pressure error
 - STATUSCHECK_NODE_UNSCHEDULABLE: Node unschedulable error
 - STATUSCHECK_NODE_UNREACHABLE: Node unreachable error
 - STATUSCHECK_NODE_NOT_READY: Node not ready error
 - STATUSCHECK_FAILED_SCHEDULING: Scheduler failure error
 - STATUSCHECK_KUBECTL_CONNECTION_ERR: Kubectl connection error
 - STATUSCHECK_KUBECTL_PID_KILLED: Kubectl process killed error
 - STATUSCHECK_KUBECTL_CLIENT_FETCH_ERR: Kubectl client fetch err
 - UNKNOWN_ERROR: Could not determine error and phase
 - STATUSCHECK_UNKNOWN: Status Check error unknown
 - STATUSCHECK_UNKNOWN_UNSCHEDULABLE: Container is unschedulable due to unknown reasons
 - STATUSCHECK_CONTAINER_WAITING_UNKNOWN: Container is waiting due to unknown reason
 - STATUSCHECK_UNKNOWN_EVENT: Container event reason unknown
 - DEPLOY_UNKNOWN: Deploy failed due to unknown reason
 - SYNC_UNKNOWN: SYNC failed due to known reason

 - DEVINIT_UNKNOWN: Dev Init failed due to unknown reason
 - CLEANUP_UNKNOWN: Cleanup failed due to unknown reason

 - DEVINIT_REGISTER_BUILD_DEPS: Failed to configure watcher for build dependencies in dev loop

get.summary: Returns all the events of the current Skaffold execution from the start

post.summary: EXPERIMENTAL. It allows for custom events to be implemented in custom builders for example.
Allows for a single execution of some or all of the phases (build, sync, deploy) in case autoBuild, autoDeploy or autoSync are disabled.

get.summary: Returns the state of the current Skaffold execution

put.summary: Allows for enabling or disabling automatic sync trigger

protoActionableErr.description: `ActionableErr` defines an error that occurred along with an optional list of suggestions

protoBuildEvent.description:
`BuildEvent` describes the build status per artifact, and will be emitted by Skaffold anytime a build starts or finishes, successfully or not.
If the build fails, an error will be attached to the event.

additional.description: Additional key value pairs to describe the deploy pipeline

artifacts.description:
A map of `artifact name -> build-state`. Artifact name is defined in the `skaffold.yaml`. The `build-state` can be:
- `"Not started"`: not yet started
- `"In progress"`: build started
- `"Complete"`: build succeeded
- `"Failed"`: build failed

protoBuildState.description: `BuildState` maps Skaffold artifacts to their current build states

protoBuildType.description:
Enum indicating build type i.e. local, cluster vs GCB
- UNKNOWN_BUILD_TYPE: Could not determine Build Type
 - CLUSTER: Cluster Build
 - GCB: GCB Build
 - LOCAL: Local Build

protoBuilderType.description:
Enum indicating builders used
- UNKNOWN_BUILDER_TYPE: Could not determine builder type
 - JIB: JIB Builder
 - BAZEL: Bazel Builder
 - BUILDPACKS: Buildpacks Builder
 - CUSTOM: Custom Builder
 - KANIKO: Kaniko Builder
 - DOCKER: Docker Builder

protoClusterType.description:
Enum indicating cluster type the application is deployed to
- UNKNOWN_CLUSTER_TYPE: Could not determine Cluster Type
 - MINIKUBE: Minikube Cluster
 - GKE: GKE cluster
 - OTHER: All Cluster except Minikube and GKE

protoDebuggingContainerEvent.description: DebuggingContainerEvent is raised when a debugging container is started or terminated

protoDeployEvent.description:
`DeployEvent` represents the status of a deployment, and is emitted by Skaffold
anytime a deployment starts or completes, successfully or not.

protoDeployState.description: `DeployState` describes the status of the current deploy

protoDeployerType.description:
Enum indicating deploy tools used
- UNKNOWN_DEPLOYER_TYPE: Could not determine Deployer Type
 - HELM: Helm Deployer
 - KUSTOMIZE: Kustomize Deployer
 - KUBECTL: Kubectl Deployer

protoDevLoopEvent.description: `DevLoopEvent` marks the start and end of a dev loop.

protoEvent.description:
`Event` describes an event in the Skaffold process.
It is one of MetaEvent, BuildEvent, DeployEvent, PortEvent, StatusCheckEvent, ResourceStatusCheckEvent, FileSyncEvent, or DebuggingContainerEvent.

protoFileSyncState.description: `FileSyncState` contains the status of the current file sync

protoIntent.description: Intent represents user intents for a given phase.

protoLogEntry.description: LogEntry describes an event and a string description of the event.

entry.description: entry, for example: `"Starting Skaffold: {Version:v0.39.0-16-g5bb7c9e0 ConfigVersion:skaffold/v1 GitVersion: GitCommit:5bb7c9e078e4d522a5ffc42a2f1274fd17d75902 GitTreeState:dirty BuildDate01:29Z GoVersion:go1.13rc1 Compiler:gc Platform:linux/amd64}"`

additional.description: Additional key value pairs to describe the build pipeline

protoPortEvent.description: PortEvent Event describes each port forwarding event.

protoResourceStatusCheckEvent.description:
A Resource StatusCheck Event, indicates progress for each kubernetes deployment.
For every resource, there will be exactly one event with `status` *Succeeded* or *Failed* event.
There can be multiple events with `status` *Pending*.
Skaffold polls for resource status every 0.5 second. If the resource status changes, an event with `status` Pending, Complete and Failed
will be sent with the new status.

protoState.description: `State` represents the current state of the Skaffold components

protoStatusCheckEvent.description: `StatusCheckEvent` describes if the status check for kubernetes rollout has started, is in progress, has succeeded or failed.

resources.description:
A map of `resource name -> status-check-state`. Where `resource-name` is the kubernetes resource name. The `status-check-state` can be
- `"Not started"`: indicates that `status-check` has just started.
- `"In progress"`: InProgress is sent after every resource check is complete.
- `"Succeeded"`: - `"Failed"`:

protoStatusCheckState.description: `StatusCheckState` describes the state of status check of current deployed resources.
